  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package conforms to the Minimal profile and carries a content hash but no digital signature, leaving structural integrity unverifiable (W-SI-01). All 13 credibility factors are addressed; seven are formally assessed and six are flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Despite factor gaps, the decision record reflects an accepted outcome for synthetic adversarial testing purposes.",
